d":"102f1ad427ab37238ac3ca2cdda291f1bc4a9ac0","tid":1408354,"uid":31215,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-04T17:17:43.000Z","msg":"後果自負英文版？"},{"pid":"6129c1ecb2f81d8082305a80381197426aef0b3c","tid":1408354,"uid":72457,"like":7,"dislike":0,"score":7,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-04T17:23:17.000Z","msg":"Hong Kong is one of the most significan: business centres on the planet and should be able to flourish and thrive on its own without answering to China. There is no doubt that the government in Mainland China will fight as hard as to implement their controversial policies and maintain as large control over HK just as they have on other territories like Tibet. It is possible that they may even accept to negotiate with the protesters and make a few small concessions in their policies. However, they are proven that they see the HK people as subjects and have no respect to their right to self-determination. It is a rare cpportunity to be able to unify so many ppl for such large demonstrations so it's essential to capitalise on these rare moments in history and make real change before the opportunity passes us by.<br />\n香港是地球上最重要的商業中心之一，應該能夠在沒有回答中國的情況下自己蓬勃發展。 毫無疑問，中國大陸政府將努力實施其有爭議的政策，並像對待西藏等其他地區一樣維持對香港的大規模控制。 他們甚至可能接受與抗議者談判並在其政策中作出一些小的讓步。 然而，他們證明他們認為香港人是主體，不尊重他們的自決權。 如此大規模的示威活動能夠統一這麼多人，這是一個難得的機會，因此必須利用歷史上的這些罕見時刻，並在機會過去之前做出真正的改變。"},{"pid":"96d3b93af13c034770a3f2d4daf329e0cdb8529f","tid":1408354,"uid":280989,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f5ea9cbce12e093c55f7e833e35e2e1af3f0b187","tid":1408354,"uid":14494,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-08-04T17:14:27.000Z","msg":"今次堅定流<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/wonder.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-08-04T17:24:43.000Z","msg":"<a href=\"https://anewspost.com/anonymous-message-to-the-people-of-hong-kong/?fbclid=IwAR262lD_mJlQSXm22by8CCEpFmW1eeEmWZ-4ahNwwzf4BlBblyfqEQBQc14\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fanews